    "chapter": "1. \n \n dog is barking at the postman.",
    "content": "r. \nTake turns and read out the story. \nEnjoy by adding actions to what you say.\nLet us learn\nLet us learn\nRead the following lines.\nA pigeon and an ant became friends.\nNotice that we used ‘a’ before pigeon and ‘an’ before ‘ant’. \nWe use ‘a’ before singular nouns that begin with \nconsonants. ‘An’ is used before singular nouns"
