    "chapter": "Chapter12. Chandrayaan",
    "content": "121\nSantoor │ Class 3\nNandini said, “Very good. Yes, a \nrocket is used to reach the Moon.”\nRani asked, “What does Chandrayaan \nmean?”\nNandini replied, “Chandra means Moon \nand Yaan means vehicle. On 23 August, \n2023, India became the first country to \nland on the far side of the Moon.”\nRani jumped with excitement and \nsaid, “Can I go to the Moon, too?”\nNandini smiled, \n“Maybe, one day.”"
