    "subject": "Math",
    "page": 102,
    "chapter": "Maths Mela | Class 3",
    "content": "ne equals 18.\n \n2 × 9 = 18\nThere are 18 laddoos.\n3 + 3 + 3 + 3 + 3 + 3 + 3 = ...... .\nOr, 6 times 3 equals 18.\nOr, 6 × 3 = 18\nThere are 18 laddoos.\nWait Dhara!\nLet the shopkeeper \narrange them in a \nbox.\nBappa, Our \nAtya likes \nladdoos. Let’s \nbuy some.\n1, 2, 3, 4,...\noh I am getting \nconfused in \ncounting them!\nSure!\nJaga\nnnat\nh Sw\neet\n S\nho\np"
