    "id": "m6309",
    "subject": "Math",
    "page": 126,
    "chapter": "Maths Mela | Class 3",
    "content": "‘Let us share the objects \nequally. I will keep the fruits, you \nkeep the tree. I will keep the lamp \nduring the night, you can keep \nit during the day. I will keep the \nblanket for half the year during \nwinter. You can keep it for half the \nyear during summer.’ Bala agreed.\nIs this a fair way of sharing? Is there \nanother way to share it fairly?"
