    "page": 66,
    "chapter": "Our Wondrous World | Class 3",
    "content": "ong, thin and flat.”\nThe pulses (dal) we eat — toor (pigeon peas), masoor (red \nlentils), moong (green gram) and urad (black gram) — are \nall seeds of shrubs.\n \nToor \nMasoor \nMoong \nUrad \n2025-26"
